article.headline: N. Dakota St. 65, Towson 48
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Mike Felt came off the bench to score 16 points and lead North Dakota State to a 65-48 victory over Towson Saturday night. The Bison of the Summit League won for the eighth time in the last 10 games. North Dakota State (9-3) led 28-25 at halftime but outscored Towson 11-2 to open the second half. The Tigers (4-7) got back within six points, 39-33, but drew no closer. Felt shot 5 for 8 from the floor, 3 of 6 on 3-pointers and 3 for 3 at the foul line. He got double-figure help from Chris Kading (11 points) and Taylor Braun (10). North Dakota State hit 43.8 percent from the field, making 21 of 48 shots. Towson was just 19 for 56 (33.9 percent). The Bison made 17 of 19 foul shots, Towson 4 of 10. Mike Burwell led the Tigers with 14 points.
